# Styling Guidelines

Use the [Appearance](mdc:ii/modules/common/Appearance.qml) singleton for all styling. Never hardcode colors, sizes, or fonts.

## Colors

Access colors via `Appearance.colors`:
- `Appearance.colors.colLayer0` - Background layer 0
- `Appearance.colors.colLayer1` - Background layer 1
- `Appearance.colors.colOnLayer0` - Text on layer 0
- `Appearance.colors.colSubtext` - Secondary text
- `Appearance.m3colors.*` - Material Design 3 colors

## Sizes

Access sizes via `Appearance.sizes`:
- `Appearance.sizes.sidebarWidth` - Sidebar width
- `Appearance.sizes.elevationMargin` - Elevation margin
- `Appearance.sizes.hyprlandGapsOut` - Hyprland gaps

## Fonts

Access fonts via `Appearance.font`:
- `Appearance.font.pixelSize.smaller`
- `Appearance.font.pixelSize.small`
- `Appearance.font.pixelSize.normal`
- `Appearance.font.pixelSize.larger`

## Rounding

Access border radius via `Appearance.rounding`:
- `Appearance.rounding.small`
- `Appearance.rounding.normal`
- `Appearance.rounding.large`

## Animations

Use `Appearance.animation` for consistent animations:

```qml
Behavior on property {
    animation: Appearance.animation.elementMoveFast.numberAnimation.createObject(this)
}
```

## Shadows

Use `StyledRectangularShadow` component for shadows:

```qml
StyledRectangularShadow {
    target: targetItem
}
```

## Material Icons

Use `MaterialSymbol` component for Material Design icons:

```qml
MaterialSymbol {
    text: "icon_name"
    color: Appearance.colors.colOnLayer0
    iconSize: Appearance.font.pixelSize.larger
}
```

## Styled Components

Use styled components from `qs.modules.common.widgets`:
- `StyledText` - Text with proper styling
- `StyledRectangularShadow` - Shadow component
- `MaterialSymbol` - Material Design icons
